Preheat your #oven{} to 240°C/220°C fan/gas mark 9.

Pour a glug of @oil{to taste} onto a #baking tray{} (to coat the bottom) and pop into
the oven to heat.

Boil a large #pot{} of salted water for the @potatoes{3}.

Chop the potatoes lengthways into 1cm slices, then into 1cm wide chips (no need to peel).

Add the potatoes to the boiling water and cook until fork tender, ~{7-8%minutes}.

> TIP: If you're in a hurry you can boil the water in your kettle.

Zest and halve the @lemon{1}.

Finely chop the @parsley{5%g} (stalks and all).

In a #medium bowl{} mix the lemon zest, @breadcrumbs{1%pack}, 1 tbsp oil (double for 4p)
and half the parsley. Season with @salt{to taste} and @pepper{to taste}.

Lay the @hale{250%g} onto a separate (lined) #baking tray{}. IMPORTANT: Wash hands
and equipment after handling raw fish.

Spread half the @mayo{2%sachets} over the top of the fish. Spoon on the breadcrumb
mixture, pressing it down with a #spoon{}. Drizzle with oil and set aside.

Once the chips are done, drain in a #colander{} and pop back in the pot.

Toss with a pinch of salt and 1 tbsp @flour{to taste} (double for 4p).

Carefully remove the tray from the oven. Add the chips and carefully toss to coat
in the oil.

Roast on the top shelf of the oven until golden, ~{25-30%minutes}. Turn halfway
through.

When halfway cooked, pop the fish on the middle shelf of the oven. Bake for
~{10-15%minutes}. IMPORTANT: Fish is cooked when opaque in the middle.

== Broccoli ==

Meanwhile, cut half the @broccoli{½} (double for 4p) into florets. Halve larger
florets.

Peel and grate @garlic{1} (or use a #garlic press{}). Pick @mint{5%g} leaves from
stalks and roughly chop (discard the stalks).

Place a #pan{} over high heat with a drizzle of oil.

Once hot, fry chopped broccoli for ~{2-3%minutes}.

Add garlic, lower heat to medium and cook for ~{1%minute}. Add a splash of
@water{to taste} and cover with a #lid{} or #foil{}. Cook until tender,
~{4-5%minutes}. Stir in the mint.

== Lemon Parsley Mayo ==

In a #small bowl{} mix the remaining parsley and mayo.

Season to taste with salt, pepper and lemon juice.

Chop any remaining lemon into wedges.

== To Serve ==

When everything is ready, plate up the broccoli alongside your fish and chips.

Finish with a dollop of lemon parsley mayo.

Serve lemon wedges alongside.